1
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,138
[METAL SCRAPING]

2
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:41,327
[BRADLEY AND GREED GRUNTING]

3
00:01:41,327 --> 00:01:42,200
[BRADLEY'S WIFE]
Darling!

4
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,239
You and Selim, stay back!

5
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:47,739
Well... Maybe you
can explain this, Wrath.

6
00:01:47,772 --> 00:01:50,072
[GREED]
What the hell is
happening to me?

7
00:01:50,105 --> 00:01:52,005
Why am I seeing these things?

8
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:56,005
They keep clawing
at the inside of my skull!

9
00:01:56,039 --> 00:01:58,239
And why are you there?

10
00:01:58,272 --> 00:02:01,339
Why do I remember you, Bradley?!

11
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:03,839
Tell me!

12
00:02:03,872 --> 00:02:07,705
Why did you destroy
my possessions?!

13
00:02:08,839 --> 00:02:11,139
You miss your things?

14
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:14,339
[BRADLEY]
You're a foolish pack rat
clinging to garbage, Greed.

15
00:02:14,372 --> 00:02:16,705
Quit craving the past!

16
00:02:17,072 --> 00:02:18,805
Bastard!

17
00:02:18,939 --> 00:02:19,939
[CUP SHATTERS]

18
00:02:20,172 --> 00:02:23,772
[SWORD CUTS THROUGH THE AIR]

19
00:02:30,205 --> 00:02:31,205
[PLATE SHATTERS]

20
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:36,172
[GREED YELLS IN AGONY]

21
00:02:42,072 --> 00:02:43,405
[GREED YELLS]

22
00:02:45,772 --> 00:02:46,939
[GREED SCREAMS]

23
00:02:46,972 --> 00:02:48,005
[SWORD CUTS THROUGH THE AIR]

24
00:02:51,472 --> 00:02:53,739
[SWORD BREAKS]

25
00:02:59,105 --> 00:03:00,839
[WINDOW SHATTERS]

26
00:03:05,105 --> 00:03:06,439
[BUTLER]
Fuhrer Bradley!

27
00:03:06,472 --> 00:03:09,205
Madam Bradley...!
Are you and Selim alright?

28
00:03:09,239 --> 00:03:11,039
[BRADLEY'S WIFE]
Ye... yes.

29
00:03:11,072 --> 00:03:12,772
[BUTLER]
I'm terribly sorry, sir.

30
00:03:12,805 --> 00:03:14,939
He overpowered
the security patrol.

31
00:03:14,972 --> 00:03:17,072
[BRADLEY]
Yes. I'm not surprised...

32
00:03:17,105 --> 00:03:19,339
He came close
to overpowering me.

33
00:03:19,372 --> 00:03:21,239
Oh, my.

34
00:03:33,566 --> 00:03:34,399
[OLIVIER]
Father...

35
00:03:34,399 --> 00:03:36,432
I demand you retire.

36
00:03:38,499 --> 00:03:39,799
Oh, Olivier.

37
00:03:39,832 --> 00:03:42,632
[PHILLIP]
It's been years since
we've last seen one another

38
00:03:42,666 --> 00:03:45,032
and that's all
you have to say to me?

39
00:03:45,066 --> 00:03:47,132
[OLIVIER]
I'll head
the family from now on.

40
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:48,666
You should spend
your final doddering,

41
00:03:48,699 --> 00:03:50,566
frail years in comfort.

42
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:52,166
Thank you for your concern.

43
00:03:52,199 --> 00:03:54,366
But I had planned to
make Alex my successor.

44
00:03:54,399 --> 00:03:57,066
You mean that
sniveling jellyfish...?

45
00:03:57,099 --> 00:03:59,399
Leave the family
affairs to me.

46
00:03:59,432 --> 00:04:02,599
Why not take a long
vacation in a foreign land?

47
00:04:02,632 --> 00:04:04,332
Alex as the head...?

48
00:04:04,366 --> 00:04:07,199
Would you truly be able
to relax leaving things to him?

49
00:04:07,232 --> 00:04:08,499
[SOMEONE KNOCKS AT THE DOOR]

50
00:04:12,399 --> 00:04:13,532
Olivier.

51
00:04:13,566 --> 00:04:15,399
I didn't know you
had planned to visit.

52
00:04:15,432 --> 00:04:18,166
[PHILLIP]
Ohhhh, Alex...
Perfect timing!

53
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:18,866
Oh?

54
00:04:18,899 --> 00:04:20,732
Engage your sister in combat.

55
00:04:20,766 --> 00:04:22,066
Huh?

56
00:04:22,099 --> 00:04:25,299
[PHILLIP]
The victor shall earn my
title as head of the family.

57
00:04:25,332 --> 00:04:27,299
Do you find this
acceptable, Olivier?

58
00:04:27,332 --> 00:04:28,332
Yes.

59
00:04:28,366 --> 00:04:30,366
I'd have it no other way.

60
00:04:30,766 --> 00:04:32,999
[PHILLIP]
Olivier insists that I retire

61
00:04:33,032 --> 00:04:35,366
and take a sojourn
in a foreign land.

62
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:36,366
She what?

63
00:04:37,566 --> 00:04:40,366
How can you treat
Father with such insolence?

64
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:41,666
For shame.

65
00:04:41,699 --> 00:04:44,166
You've given me no choice!

66
00:04:49,032 --> 00:04:50,266
Understand, sister...

67
00:04:50,299 --> 00:04:53,699
I intend to use every ounce of
my body and soul to fight you.

68
00:04:53,732 --> 00:04:55,366
[ARMSTRONG'S FOOT
SLAMS ON THE FLOOR]

69
00:04:55,399 --> 00:04:57,332
Don't patronize me, Alex...

70
00:04:57,366 --> 00:05:00,199
Your bloated muscles are
worthless without a spine.

71
00:05:00,232 --> 00:05:01,532
[OLIVIER AND ARMSTRONG GRUNTING]

72
00:05:01,566 --> 00:05:03,566
Shall we prepare
for our respite?

73
00:05:03,599 --> 00:05:05,032
--Yes.
--Yes.

74
00:05:06,532 --> 00:05:08,366
[OLIVIER]
Get over here!

75
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:11,999
So, which exotic
locale might you suggest?

76
00:05:12,032 --> 00:05:14,366
Well, I'm intrigued to
see what Xing is like...

77
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:17,699
I've heard that they have
tantalizing cuisine there.

78
00:05:17,732 --> 00:05:21,066
Then Xing it is...
Fine with you, Catherine?

79
00:05:21,099 --> 00:05:22,666
Sure...
Sounds exciting.

80
00:05:22,699 --> 00:05:24,432
[DOOR BENDS AND BREAKS OPEN]

81
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:26,199
[ARMSTRONG YELLS]

82
00:05:28,566 --> 00:05:32,232
[ARMSTRONG]
Nooo...! Enouuuugh!

83
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:34,266
Please...! Mercy!

84
00:05:34,299 --> 00:05:35,999
[OLIVIER]
No take-backs, Alex!

85
00:05:36,032 --> 00:05:37,532
Are you trying to kill me?

86
00:05:37,566 --> 00:05:40,266
What tipped
you off, moron?

87
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:42,199
Try to hang
in there, Alex.

88
00:05:42,232 --> 00:05:43,266
[ARMSTRONG GRUNTS]

89
00:05:44,566 --> 00:05:47,266
[CATHERINE]
What sort of souvenirs
should we bring back for them?

90
00:05:47,299 --> 00:05:51,099
[PHILLIP]
Statues seem the most fitting...
Large and solid statues.

91
00:05:51,132 --> 00:05:53,766
Well in that case,
I want a statue too, then.

92
00:05:53,799 --> 00:05:55,199
Oh?

93
00:05:55,366 --> 00:05:56,599
[WATER SPLASHES]

94
00:05:58,032 --> 00:05:59,066
[ARMSTRONG YELLS]

95
00:05:59,099 --> 00:06:00,632
[CAR ACCELERATING]

96
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:04,032
[ARMSTRONG]
Nooooooo!

97
00:06:04,732 --> 00:06:07,599
[ARMSTRONG SLAMS INTO FIREPLACE]

98
00:06:08,199 --> 00:06:09,599
[ARMSTRONG GRUNTING IN AGONY]

99
00:06:09,632 --> 00:06:12,232
And that settles that.

100
00:06:12,332 --> 00:06:14,032
[SWORD SCRAPES SHEATH]

101
00:06:14,732 --> 00:06:18,366
[ARMSTRONG GRUNTING]

102
00:06:18,399 --> 00:06:23,466
I'm the rightful successor.
The family belongs to me.

103
00:06:23,499 --> 00:06:24,666
[ARMSTRONG]
Olivier...

104
00:06:24,699 --> 00:06:28,699
Why have you become so convivial
with the senior officers?

105
00:06:28,732 --> 00:06:31,266
How can you...?
The senior staff is in league--

106
00:06:31,299 --> 00:06:34,566
I can determine their
complicity with my own eyes.

107
00:06:34,599 --> 00:06:36,266
And what have
your eyes seen...?

108
00:06:36,299 --> 00:06:38,999
Have you exiled Mother
and Father to a foreign land,

109
00:06:39,032 --> 00:06:41,432
so they can't
be taken hostage?

110
00:06:44,332 --> 00:06:45,699
Get out, loser...

111
00:06:45,732 --> 00:06:49,066
You'll stink up my
mansion with your cowardice.

112
00:06:54,032 --> 00:06:56,066
[STEAM RELEASES]

113
00:07:12,299 --> 00:07:15,232
[HALLING]
And where are you
headed, young lady?

114
00:07:15,266 --> 00:07:17,399
You're walking straight
towards the edge of town...

115
00:07:17,432 --> 00:07:20,132
And there's nothing but
desert for hundreds of miles.

116
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:23,532
Well, I... I'm traveling
back to my own country.

117
00:07:23,566 --> 00:07:24,499
Oh, yeah?

118
00:07:24,532 --> 00:07:26,266
Yes... I'm from Xing.

119
00:07:26,299 --> 00:07:28,066
Across the desert?

120
00:07:28,099 --> 00:07:29,066
Uh-huh.

121
00:07:29,099 --> 00:07:30,199
Wait, you mean
you're gonna

122
00:07:30,232 --> 00:07:32,266
cross the desert
all by yourself?

123
00:07:32,299 --> 00:07:33,166
Yeah.

124
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:35,499
[CROWD GASPS]

125
00:07:35,532 --> 00:07:36,766
Alright, everyone.

126
00:07:36,799 --> 00:07:40,599
[HALLING]
Let's help her out.
Hand over any extra food.

127
00:07:40,632 --> 00:07:41,499
You don't need to--

128
00:07:41,532 --> 00:07:43,332
[KAYAL]
Hey, don't
worry about it.

129
00:07:43,366 --> 00:07:44,999
Why don't you leave tomorrow?

130
00:07:45,032 --> 00:07:46,566
Stay the night and
get some good rest.

131
00:07:46,599 --> 00:07:48,666
You're more than
welcome to use our bath.

132
00:07:48,699 --> 00:07:50,766
We can make
you some dinner.

133
00:07:50,799 --> 00:07:51,999
[HALLING]
What about you, Steve...?

134
00:07:52,032 --> 00:07:54,732
You've got some empty rooms
now. Why don't you put her up?

135
00:07:54,766 --> 00:07:56,232
[STEVE]
Yeah, sure thing...

136
00:07:56,266 --> 00:07:58,999
She'd be nice and comfy
in Emmy's old room.

137
00:07:59,032 --> 00:08:01,199
[MAN 1]
Did Emmy already leave
for college in Central?

138
00:08:01,232 --> 00:08:04,232
I guess the apple falls pretty
far from the tree after all.

139
00:08:04,266 --> 00:08:05,332
[STEVE]
I guess so.

140
00:08:05,366 --> 00:08:08,666
We'll have to feed your
adorable little kitty, too.

141
00:08:08,699 --> 00:08:10,299
[SHAO MAY YELPS]

142
00:08:10,332 --> 00:08:12,132
Oh! She's certainly hungry.

143
00:08:12,166 --> 00:08:14,366
I get the feeling that
she thinks you're her food.

144
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:16,399
Oh, hush. Don't be silly...

145
00:08:16,432 --> 00:08:18,732
You don't eat
people, do you, kitty?

146
00:08:18,766 --> 00:08:19,566
[SHAO MAY YELPS]

147
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:22,099
Y'see...? She said
you look delicious.

148
00:08:22,132 --> 00:08:24,132
[CROWD LAUGHS]

149
00:08:26,066 --> 00:08:28,332
[ENVY]
They sure are nice, huh?

150
00:08:28,366 --> 00:08:30,399
And you don't even
wanna help them?

151
00:08:30,432 --> 00:08:33,399
Well, that's probably
for the best...

152
00:08:33,432 --> 00:08:35,999
I do wonder...
What's your emperor gonna think

153
00:08:36,032 --> 00:08:38,132
when you hand over
a half-dead Homunculus?

154
00:08:38,166 --> 00:08:40,666
I doubt it's gonna do
your clan much good.

155
00:08:42,299 --> 00:08:44,132
But you could
go to Central...

156
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:45,532
I mean, that's
where you can learn

157
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:48,099
the true way to
gain immortality...

158
00:08:48,132 --> 00:08:52,266
You could even help save
all of these people's lives.

159
00:08:52,299 --> 00:08:53,766
Oh, well...

160
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:56,266
Why should you care if
they live or die anyway?

161
00:08:56,299 --> 00:08:58,966
It's not like it's
your country or anything.

162
00:09:01,266 --> 00:09:04,599
[SHAO MAY SQUEALING]

163
00:09:07,132 --> 00:09:10,432
[MAY CHANG]
I'm sorry. Thank you
so much for your kindness!

164
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:11,999
Wait, where are you going?

165
00:09:12,032 --> 00:09:13,699
[MAY CHANG]
I've gotta get
back to Central!

166
00:09:13,732 --> 00:09:16,166
I've got some
unfinished business!

167
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:18,532
[ENVY THINKING]
<i>Heh, Idiot...</i>

168
00:09:18,566 --> 00:09:22,766
<i>I'm gonna stuff you in</i>
<i>a jar once we get to Central.</i>

169
00:09:22,799 --> 00:09:25,366
<i>I just need</i>
<i>a Philosopher's Stone...</i>

170
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:28,032
<i>After that,</i>
<i>I'll be whole again...</i>

171
00:09:28,066 --> 00:09:31,266
<i>Just wait 'til I get a stone.</i>

172
00:09:31,732 --> 00:09:33,732
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

173
00:09:38,095 --> 00:09:40,095
[NARRATOR]
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

174
00:09:51,595 --> 00:09:52,661
[DARIUS]
Where are we?

175
00:09:52,695 --> 00:09:55,628
[ED]
We've used this place
as a hideout before.

176
00:09:55,661 --> 00:09:57,728
And you're positive
that your brother's here?

177
00:09:57,761 --> 00:09:58,661
Oh, yeah...

178
00:09:58,695 --> 00:10:01,161
I know Al better
than he knows himself.

179
00:10:01,195 --> 00:10:03,695
This is the only
place he would be.

180
00:10:04,195 --> 00:10:05,161
[DARIUS]
Hey...

181
00:10:05,195 --> 00:10:06,895
There's nobody here!

182
00:10:06,928 --> 00:10:09,061
Yeah, you really
know your brother.

183
00:10:09,095 --> 00:10:13,228
We busted our tails for hundreds
of miles for an empty house?

184
00:10:13,761 --> 00:10:15,061
[HEINKEL SNIFFS]

185
00:10:15,328 --> 00:10:16,561
[HEINKEL COCKS GUN]

186
00:10:16,895 --> 00:10:17,895
[DARIUS GASPS]

187
00:10:19,328 --> 00:10:23,261
[APPROACHING FOOTSTEPS]

188
00:10:23,295 --> 00:10:24,695
[ED STAMMERS]

189
00:10:27,795 --> 00:10:29,128
[BODY THUDS
ONTO THE FLOOR]

190
00:10:31,961 --> 00:10:34,295
Ling...! I mean, Greed!

191
00:10:34,328 --> 00:10:35,928
[LING'S STOMACH GROWLS]

192
00:10:37,128 --> 00:10:40,161
Hungry... Need, food.

193
00:10:40,195 --> 00:10:42,195
Heh... No, it's Ling.

194
00:10:42,761 --> 00:10:49,195
[LING EATING QUICKLY]

195
00:10:49,228 --> 00:10:51,061
[LING LAUGHING]

196
00:10:52,028 --> 00:10:53,161
Well, that
did the trick!

197
00:10:53,195 --> 00:10:55,161
Thanks, Edward...
You're too kind.

198
00:10:55,195 --> 00:10:58,061
[ED]
It's amazing that
you're not a giant fat-ass.

199
00:10:58,095 --> 00:11:00,161
He ate all
of our rations.

200
00:11:00,195 --> 00:11:02,028
Are you gonna
introduce me to your pals?

201
00:11:02,061 --> 00:11:03,028
That's Mr. Gorill--

202
00:11:03,061 --> 00:11:04,161
My name's Darius!

203
00:11:04,195 --> 00:11:05,628
And I'm Heinkel...

204
00:11:05,661 --> 00:11:06,828
We're ex-military...

205
00:11:06,861 --> 00:11:10,295
But we wound up getting stuck
working with this kid somehow.

206
00:11:10,328 --> 00:11:12,295
Now what's
this guy's story?

207
00:11:12,328 --> 00:11:13,661
Well, let's see.

208
00:11:13,695 --> 00:11:15,628
It's really kind of complicated.

209
00:11:15,661 --> 00:11:17,528
I'm a Homunculus.

210
00:11:17,561 --> 00:11:18,261
--Huh?
--Huh?

211
00:11:18,295 --> 00:11:20,028
Can you try to
be more discrete?!

212
00:11:20,061 --> 00:11:21,561
Seriously?!

213
00:11:21,595 --> 00:11:23,595
It'll take too
long to explain...

214
00:11:23,628 --> 00:11:26,895
And what are you doing here,
I thought you'd be in Central.

215
00:11:26,928 --> 00:11:27,995
Well, to put it lightly,

216
00:11:28,028 --> 00:11:30,761
Greed had a falling out
with the other Homunculi...

217
00:11:30,795 --> 00:11:32,961
So I took advantage
of his confusion,

218
00:11:32,995 --> 00:11:35,961
and managed to regain
control of my body.

219
00:11:35,995 --> 00:11:37,795
I had to get
out of Central...

220
00:11:37,828 --> 00:11:40,828
And needed someplace
close by to hide... So I--

221
00:11:40,861 --> 00:11:41,861
[LING WINCING IN PAIN]

222
00:11:41,895 --> 00:11:43,161
What's the matter?

223
00:11:43,195 --> 00:11:46,895
It's Greed...
He's starting to fight back.

224
00:11:46,928 --> 00:11:47,728
[ED]
Hey!

225
00:11:47,761 --> 00:11:49,861
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

226
00:11:49,895 --> 00:11:53,128
Fight him back you idiot!
Don't let him overpower you!

227
00:11:53,161 --> 00:11:54,028
Jeez!

228
00:11:54,061 --> 00:11:57,795
Listen... That guy
beneath Central...

229
00:11:57,828 --> 00:11:59,761
The one that they
call their father...

230
00:11:59,795 --> 00:12:04,061
He's gonna open the portal...
On the "day of reckoning."

231
00:12:04,095 --> 00:12:06,295
I could be
wrong about this...

232
00:12:06,328 --> 00:12:09,061
...but I think you and Al
should jump in when he does.

233
00:12:09,095 --> 00:12:11,995
It's the best chance you have
to get your bodies back.

234
00:12:12,028 --> 00:12:13,061
[ED GASPS]

235
00:12:14,228 --> 00:12:17,728
Wait a minute. That makes
sense and everything but...

236
00:12:17,761 --> 00:12:20,628
...there's a toll that must
be paid to even open the portal.

237
00:12:20,661 --> 00:12:21,928
[ED GASPS]

238
00:12:21,961 --> 00:12:26,161
[ED THINKING]
<i>And why...? Why is</i>
<i>he opening the portal?</i>

239
00:12:26,195 --> 00:12:27,828
[ED]
This "day of reckoning"...

240
00:12:27,861 --> 00:12:30,095
Do you know the exact
day he's gonna open it?

241
00:12:30,128 --> 00:12:31,528
It's happening--

242
00:12:31,561 --> 00:12:32,095
[LING WINCING IN PAIN]

243
00:12:32,128 --> 00:12:33,128
Ling?

244
00:12:33,161 --> 00:12:34,828
C'mon!

245
00:12:34,861 --> 00:12:39,695
Damn it... I can't
hold him much longer.

246
00:12:39,728 --> 00:12:41,261
The message...

247
00:12:42,228 --> 00:12:45,761
You got it to Lan Fan, right?
You gave her the message?

248
00:12:45,795 --> 00:12:47,661
The message...?

249
00:12:50,195 --> 00:12:53,028
Al gave it to her...
And she's doing alright...

250
00:12:53,061 --> 00:12:55,661
I don't know where
she is, but she's safe.

251
00:12:55,695 --> 00:12:58,161
Thank you, Ed.
That's good to hear.

252
00:12:58,195 --> 00:12:59,295
[LING WINCING IN PAIN]

253
00:12:59,328 --> 00:13:00,595
Ling!

254
00:13:00,628 --> 00:13:02,561
[LING]
Sorry...

255
00:13:02,595 --> 00:13:05,761
That's it for me... I'm gone.

256
00:13:09,661 --> 00:13:11,761
[GREED GRUNTS]

257
00:13:11,795 --> 00:13:14,628
Damn...
Pain in the ass prince.

258
00:13:14,661 --> 00:13:16,995
He needs to learn to
keep his big mouth shut.

259
00:13:17,028 --> 00:13:18,161
[ED]
Is that you, Greed?

260
00:13:18,195 --> 00:13:20,161
Yeah, what
tipped you off?

261
00:13:20,195 --> 00:13:21,028
[GUN COCKS]

262
00:13:21,061 --> 00:13:22,761
[GREED]
Don't bother...

263
00:13:22,795 --> 00:13:24,861
You can't even
scratch me with that thing.

264
00:13:24,895 --> 00:13:26,095
[ED STAMMERS]

265
00:13:26,128 --> 00:13:28,595
[GREED]
Well, see ya later.

266
00:13:28,628 --> 00:13:29,628
Hey!

267
00:13:29,661 --> 00:13:32,061
Aren't you gonna
try to capture us?

268
00:13:32,095 --> 00:13:33,728
Huh?

269
00:13:33,761 --> 00:13:36,861
Were you even listening to
anything the prince told you?

270
00:13:36,895 --> 00:13:39,161
I'm working on
my solo career now.

271
00:13:39,195 --> 00:13:41,595
All these memories
came flooding back,

272
00:13:41,628 --> 00:13:44,095
and I kind of went
nuts and attacked Bradley.

273
00:13:44,128 --> 00:13:47,161
Who knows what they'd do
to me if I go crawling back...

274
00:13:47,195 --> 00:13:48,928
And I don't really
work well with others,

275
00:13:48,961 --> 00:13:50,928
so it's probably for the best.

276
00:13:50,961 --> 00:13:52,961
And that's that.

277
00:13:53,595 --> 00:13:55,661
Why don't you
team up with us?

278
00:13:55,695 --> 00:13:56,595
[FLOORBOARD SQUEAKS]

279
00:13:56,628 --> 00:13:57,695
[DARIUS AND HEINKEL]
Huh?!

280
00:13:58,761 --> 00:14:02,228
You've got nowhere to go.
Why not come with us?

281
00:14:07,928 --> 00:14:09,928
[GREED LAUGHS]

282
00:14:09,961 --> 00:14:13,261
[GREED]
Team up with you...?
You want me to follow you?

283
00:14:13,295 --> 00:14:15,028
Thanks for the laugh.

284
00:14:15,061 --> 00:14:16,261
Up yours, kid...

285
00:14:16,295 --> 00:14:19,261
This world is my
possession, not yours.

286
00:14:19,295 --> 00:14:22,061
[GREED]
Now it's a different story
if you wanna follow me...

287
00:14:22,095 --> 00:14:23,928
You're welcome
to join my team.

288
00:14:23,961 --> 00:14:26,195
[GREED LAUGHING]

289
00:14:26,228 --> 00:14:27,995
Later.

290
00:14:37,128 --> 00:14:38,828
[GREED THINKING]
<i>Team up with him?</i>

291
00:14:38,861 --> 00:14:40,761
<i>Do I look that desperate?</i>

292
00:14:40,795 --> 00:14:44,028
<i>It doesn't matter how</i>
<i>many souls I've got in me.</i>

293
00:14:44,061 --> 00:14:46,628
<i>I'm completely alone now.</i>

294
00:14:46,661 --> 00:14:51,028
[LING]
If you're gonna pout about it,
why don't you join up with Ed?

295
00:14:51,061 --> 00:14:54,628
But if you want more, you could
always give me my body back.

296
00:14:54,661 --> 00:14:56,761
I'll take my place
as emperor of Xing...

297
00:14:56,795 --> 00:14:59,595
That should be enough
to fill up your emptiness.

298
00:14:59,628 --> 00:15:01,795
[GREED]
The ruler of
a whole country?

299
00:15:01,828 --> 00:15:03,728
[LING]
Not bad, huh?

300
00:15:03,761 --> 00:15:06,928
[GREED]
Get over it...
You think too small.

301
00:15:06,961 --> 00:15:09,161
That's just not enough.

302
00:15:09,195 --> 00:15:11,928
Now ruler of the world?

303
00:15:11,961 --> 00:15:13,961
I could enjoy that.

304
00:15:14,661 --> 00:15:16,195
The whole world?

305
00:15:16,228 --> 00:15:18,495
[ED]
Hey! Ling...! Wait up!

306
00:15:19,328 --> 00:15:21,661
[GREED]
How many times
do I have to tell you?

307
00:15:21,695 --> 00:15:23,795
I'm Greed, not Ling.

308
00:15:23,828 --> 00:15:25,895
It's too difficult
to keep track of...

309
00:15:25,928 --> 00:15:27,628
I'll just call you
Greeling from now on.

310
00:15:27,661 --> 00:15:28,561
No...! You will not--

311
00:15:28,595 --> 00:15:31,261
Listen to me, Greeling...
I'll follow you.

312
00:15:31,295 --> 00:15:32,861
Huh?

313
00:15:32,895 --> 00:15:33,928
I thought about it

314
00:15:33,961 --> 00:15:36,061
and I've decided to
join your team after all...

315
00:15:36,095 --> 00:15:38,661
And since these guys seem
to follow me everywhere,

316
00:15:38,695 --> 00:15:40,895
you've got two chimeras
on your team as well.

317
00:15:40,928 --> 00:15:42,261
[DARIUS GRUNTS ANGRILY]

318
00:15:42,295 --> 00:15:44,928
[DARIUS]
Who do you think you are?!
You don't get to make that call!

319
00:15:44,961 --> 00:15:48,995
[HEINKEL]
Nobody said you were our boss,
pipsqueak! You little runt!

320
00:15:49,028 --> 00:15:50,895
Uhh...

321
00:15:51,928 --> 00:15:53,161
[ED]
I realized something...

322
00:15:53,195 --> 00:15:57,161
I've been a follower ever since
I became a dog of the military.

323
00:15:57,195 --> 00:15:59,161
I lost my pride a while back.

324
00:15:59,195 --> 00:16:02,061
So I'm already used to
rolling over on command...

325
00:16:02,095 --> 00:16:03,628
And besides...

326
00:16:03,661 --> 00:16:04,928
There's too much at stake.

327
00:16:04,961 --> 00:16:06,895
I can't let any
information you've got

328
00:16:06,928 --> 00:16:07,961
slip through the cracks.

329
00:16:07,995 --> 00:16:08,895
[ED LAUGHS]

330
00:16:08,928 --> 00:16:11,628
I really can't let
my ego get in the way.

331
00:16:12,295 --> 00:16:13,895
[GREED]
What a waste...

332
00:16:13,928 --> 00:16:15,028
You lose your temper like this

333
00:16:15,061 --> 00:16:18,895
and you're gonna lose my
information and your brother.

334
00:16:18,928 --> 00:16:21,595
[GREED LAUGHS]

335
00:16:21,628 --> 00:16:22,828
Alright, kid.

336
00:16:22,861 --> 00:16:25,761
But workin' for me means you
haveta' live in the shadows...

337
00:16:25,795 --> 00:16:27,295
I don't wanna
hear any regrets.

338
00:16:27,328 --> 00:16:28,728
Give me a break.

339
00:16:28,761 --> 00:16:30,561
I've already got
a million regrets.

340
00:16:30,595 --> 00:16:31,761
What's one more?

341
00:16:31,795 --> 00:16:33,661
--A million and one.
--A million and one.

342
00:16:33,695 --> 00:16:35,028
[GREED]
Good, then it's settled...

343
00:16:35,061 --> 00:16:37,628
So then you guys are
working for me too.

344
00:16:37,661 --> 00:16:39,628
[HEINKEL]
Doesn't seem like
we have much choice.

345
00:16:39,661 --> 00:16:42,561
[DARIUS]
I don't care who I follow
as long as they're feeding me.

346
00:16:42,595 --> 00:16:44,295
So what kind of
Chimeras are you?

347
00:16:44,328 --> 00:16:45,761
[DARIUS]
I'm part gorilla.

348
00:16:45,795 --> 00:16:46,928
[HEINKEL]
I'm part lion.

349
00:16:46,961 --> 00:16:49,061
Heh, well
that's pretty cool.

350
00:16:49,095 --> 00:16:52,861
[ED THINKING]
<i>Oh, yeah... I've still</i>
<i>got Winry's earrings.</i>

351
00:16:52,895 --> 00:16:54,728
<i>I get the feeling</i>
<i>that I won't be seeing</i>

352
00:16:54,761 --> 00:16:56,928
<i>Winry or Al for a while.</i>

353
00:16:58,761 --> 00:17:01,161
<i>The "day of reckoning", huh?</i>

354
00:17:07,758 --> 00:17:10,877
[MASON]
I've told you. You don't
have to keep coming back.

355
00:17:10,877 --> 00:17:14,044
I'll call you when Mrs. Izumi
returns from her trip.

356
00:17:14,077 --> 00:17:17,277
I can't get any work done with
you guys constantly bugging me.

357
00:17:17,311 --> 00:17:19,711
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

358
00:17:21,011 --> 00:17:22,944
Hello, Curtis Butcher Shop...

359
00:17:22,977 --> 00:17:26,977
Oh, yes, it's almost ready...
Five o'clock is fine.

360
00:17:27,011 --> 00:17:27,944
[SOLDIER 1]
We'll be back.

361
00:17:27,977 --> 00:17:31,177
Well maybe you could
buy something next time!

362
00:17:32,844 --> 00:17:33,944
Sorry 'bout that...

363
00:17:33,977 --> 00:17:37,944
The military's pretty
desperate to find you... Yeah.

364
00:17:37,977 --> 00:17:40,011
I've got a message
for you from Alphonse

365
00:17:40,044 --> 00:17:42,177
and some man
named Hohenheim.

366
00:17:43,281 --> 00:17:44,314
[CAR ACCELERATING]

367
00:17:44,881 --> 00:17:46,914
[SIG]
I see.

368
00:17:46,948 --> 00:17:49,948
That sounds like
it's pretty serious.

369
00:17:50,814 --> 00:17:53,214
Yeah... I'll pass it on.

370
00:17:53,248 --> 00:17:54,648
[PHONE CLICKS]

371
00:17:55,214 --> 00:17:57,681
The "day of reckoning", huh?

372
00:17:59,214 --> 00:18:06,048
[SCATTERED GUNFIRE]

373
00:18:06,081 --> 00:18:07,781
[SOLDIER 2]
Report to headquarters at once!

374
00:18:07,814 --> 00:18:10,681
This is lookout post B!
We're under attack!

375
00:18:10,714 --> 00:18:11,981
[HQ]
What...? Is it Drachma?

376
00:18:12,014 --> 00:18:13,081
We're not sure!

377
00:18:13,114 --> 00:18:14,314
[HQ]
How many of them are there?

378
00:18:14,348 --> 00:18:15,314
Just one!

379
00:18:15,348 --> 00:18:17,148
[HQ]
Just one...? Are you sure?

380
00:18:17,181 --> 00:18:18,248
[SOLDIER 2 SCREAMS]

381
00:18:19,914 --> 00:18:22,448
[HQ]
Hey...! Are you still there?!

382
00:18:22,481 --> 00:18:25,148
[HQ]
Point B...! Who's attacking?!

383
00:18:25,181 --> 00:18:26,848
A housewife!

384
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:31,114
[MILES]
An attack on the mountain patrol
by a mysterious woman...

385
00:18:31,148 --> 00:18:34,214
It's just the same as those
attacks twenty years ago.

386
00:18:34,248 --> 00:18:37,081
This doesn't look good
for the mountain patrol.

387
00:18:37,114 --> 00:18:40,348
[BUCCANEER]
General Armstrong's gonna
kill us when she gets back.

388
00:18:42,014 --> 00:18:43,348
[BRIGGS SOLDIER 1]
Major Miles.

389
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:45,314
[MILES]
At ease.

390
00:18:46,748 --> 00:18:50,248
[IZUMI]
Well look at this! An Ishvalan
with dark glasses and sideburns,

391
00:18:50,281 --> 00:18:51,948
and a big guy with a Mohawk...

392
00:18:51,981 --> 00:18:54,248
You look just like
they said you would.

393
00:18:54,281 --> 00:18:55,448
I was starting to wonder

394
00:18:55,481 --> 00:18:57,848
how long I'd have
to wait for you guys.

395
00:18:58,348 --> 00:19:00,181
Why don't you
tell us who you are?

396
00:19:00,214 --> 00:19:03,681
I'm no one special. Just
a housewife passing through...

397
00:19:03,714 --> 00:19:06,048
But I do have a message
for you from Alphonse.

398
00:19:06,081 --> 00:19:07,314
[BUCCANEER GRUNTS]

399
00:19:07,348 --> 00:19:09,881
Where can we talk in private?

400
00:19:10,314 --> 00:19:11,348
[FALMAN]
Yes sir.

401
00:19:11,381 --> 00:19:13,814
It's a message
from Alphonse Elric.

402
00:19:13,848 --> 00:19:16,148
It's about that day...
"The Promised Day."

403
00:19:16,181 --> 00:19:18,248
Ah, yes...
The "day of reckoning"...

404
00:19:18,281 --> 00:19:20,948
Your timing
couldn't be better.

405
00:19:20,981 --> 00:19:23,881
This is certainly
getting interesting.

406
00:19:24,314 --> 00:19:28,948
[GUNFIRE]

407
00:19:29,848 --> 00:19:31,448
[GRUMMAN]
Hello there, Rebecca!

408
00:19:31,481 --> 00:19:33,314
Your aim is looking fine,

409
00:19:33,348 --> 00:19:35,781
but not nearly as
fine as your tushie.

410
00:19:35,814 --> 00:19:36,781
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

411
00:19:36,814 --> 00:19:38,948
What do you think you're
doing, General Grumman?!

412
00:19:38,981 --> 00:19:40,048
[GRUMMAN LAUGHS]

413
00:19:40,081 --> 00:19:42,781
You've gotta keep your
guard up on the battlefield.

414
00:19:42,814 --> 00:19:43,848
But seriously...

415
00:19:43,881 --> 00:19:46,848
You're friends with
Lieutenant Hawkeye, correct?

416
00:19:46,881 --> 00:19:48,081
Huh?

417
00:19:51,448 --> 00:19:53,748
Hey Riza! Yoo-hoo! Over here!

418
00:19:53,781 --> 00:19:55,281
Long time no see, Rebecca.

419
00:19:55,314 --> 00:19:56,348
[DOG BARKS]

420
00:19:57,548 --> 00:19:58,614
[REBECCA]
I caught wind of
a rumor that they're gonna

421
00:19:58,648 --> 00:20:02,181
postpone the North versus
East training exercises.

422
00:20:02,214 --> 00:20:04,781
That little border skirmish
between Drachma and Briggs

423
00:20:04,814 --> 00:20:06,748
has thrown everything off.

424
00:20:06,781 --> 00:20:10,048
[HAWKEYE]
They've actually decided to hold
the drills in the east instead.

425
00:20:10,081 --> 00:20:12,248
I heard that from
the Fuhrer himself.

426
00:20:12,281 --> 00:20:13,214
Aww...

427
00:20:13,248 --> 00:20:15,314
It's not fair that you
got Colonel Mustang

428
00:20:15,348 --> 00:20:17,181
and now the Fuhrer.

429
00:20:17,214 --> 00:20:20,848
I think it's time you set me
up with a nice guy from Central.

430
00:20:20,881 --> 00:20:21,948
[DOG BARKS]

431
00:20:21,981 --> 00:20:24,102
[HAWKEYE]
Here. This is the
nicest guy I know.

432
00:20:24,102 --> 00:20:28,036
Oh, Hayate! How can your master
be so cold-blooded and cruel?

433
00:20:28,069 --> 00:20:30,769
[BELLS CHIMING]

434
00:20:30,802 --> 00:20:32,302
Don't doubt me, Riza!

435
00:20:32,336 --> 00:20:35,902
I'm gonna find a nice guy
and quit this lousy job!

436
00:20:35,936 --> 00:20:38,302
If you say so...
Good luck with that.

437
00:20:38,402 --> 00:20:39,369
[REBECCA GASPS]

438
00:20:40,436 --> 00:20:42,736
Make sure to tell
Lieutenant Havoc I said hello.

439
00:20:42,769 --> 00:20:43,969
[HAWKEYE]
You got it.

440
00:20:44,002 --> 00:20:45,336
See ya!

441
00:20:45,969 --> 00:20:47,336
[DOG WHINES]

442
00:20:47,369 --> 00:20:49,102
[HAWKEYE LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

443
00:20:53,069 --> 00:20:57,036
Well now... She wants me
to say "Hi." to Havoc? Huh...

444
00:20:59,002 --> 00:21:01,169
[HAVOC]
I'm waiting for
my condition to stabilize.

445
00:21:01,202 --> 00:21:03,802
But I'm thinking about
transferring back east.

446
00:21:03,836 --> 00:21:06,369
Really...? We'll
miss you around here.

447
00:21:06,402 --> 00:21:08,669
I wish I had a better
going away gift,

448
00:21:08,702 --> 00:21:10,436
but I'm sure
you'll like this.

449
00:21:10,469 --> 00:21:13,002
Here you go...
Only one per day, though.

450
00:21:13,036 --> 00:21:16,402
Aw, thanks, Lieutenant!
And I was just about to run out.

451
00:21:16,436 --> 00:21:18,169
I'll drop in again soon.

452
00:21:18,202 --> 00:21:19,169
Thank you.

453
00:21:19,202 --> 00:21:20,402
Oh.

454
00:21:20,436 --> 00:21:22,902
Rebecca wanted me
to say hello for her.

455
00:21:22,936 --> 00:21:24,302
Okay, great.

456
00:21:26,469 --> 00:21:28,369
[HAWKEYE]
Oh, and tell
the Colonel that I said hi.

457
00:21:28,402 --> 00:21:30,136
Okey-doke.

458
00:21:31,202 --> 00:21:32,302
You heard the lady.

459
00:21:32,336 --> 00:21:34,002
She says hi.

460
00:21:35,702 --> 00:21:38,002
Was it really
necessary that you hide?

461
00:21:38,036 --> 00:21:40,836
[ROY]
She and I are both under
constant surveillance...

462
00:21:40,869 --> 00:21:43,669
It'll arouse far too much
suspicion if I have any

463
00:21:43,702 --> 00:21:45,936
private contact with her.

464
00:21:47,269 --> 00:21:48,836
[HAVOC EXHALES]

465
00:21:48,869 --> 00:21:52,802
Oh, yeah... You look like
you could use one too, Colonel.

466
00:21:52,836 --> 00:21:54,902
No thanks...
I better take off.

467
00:21:54,936 --> 00:21:57,436
Oh, trust me,
you can use this one.

468
00:21:57,469 --> 00:21:58,669
Hmm...

469
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:11,136
<i>[ROY]</i>
<i>Be prepared for</i>
<i>the coming spring.</i>

470
00:22:11,169 --> 00:22:13,969
When the Promised Day arrives...

471
00:22:14,902 --> 00:22:18,069
<i>The north and the east</i>
<i>will make their move.</i>

472
00:24:03,236 --> 00:24:07,209
[NARRATOR]
<i>After the new year has</i>
<i>passed and spring is upon us,</i>

473
00:24:07,209 --> 00:24:11,076
<i>their resolution will evolve and</i>
<i>take the form of a revolution.</i>

474
00:24:11,109 --> 00:24:13,642
<i>And now the young man</i>
<i>will follow his heart</i>

475
00:24:13,676 --> 00:24:16,209
<i>straight into the lion's den.</i>

476
00:24:16,242 --> 00:24:19,676
<i>Next time on Fullmetal</i>
<i>Alchemist: Brotherhood.</i>

477
00:24:19,709 --> 00:24:23,642
<i>Episode 46:</i>
<i>"Looming Shadows."</i>

478
00:24:23,676 --> 00:24:27,142
<i>The heart is capable of moving</i>
<i>past the pain of separation...</i>

479
00:24:27,176 --> 00:24:31,076
<i>...as long as one keeps</i>
<i>moving forward as well.</i>

